speedway motorsports  wikipedia speedway motorsports from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from speedway motorsports inc jump to navigation search speedway motorsports type public traded as nyse trk industry motorsports founded  headquarters concord north carolina at charlotte motor speedway key people bruton smith founder and ceo marcus g smith president and coo products motorsport venues legends cars revenue  million usd number of employees  full time website wwwspeedwaymotorsportscom speedway motorsports inc smi is an american corporation that owns and manages racing facilities that host nascar indycar series nhra world of outlaws and other motor racing series the companys headquarters are located at charlotte motor speedway in the suburbs of charlotte nc smi owns nine racing facilities with a combined seating capacity of approximately  in addition to operating racetracks smi owns performance racing network prn us legends cars international and coowns motorsports authentics contents  history  facilities owned  notable purchases  north wilkesboro speedway  north carolina speedway  new hampshire motor speedway  kentucky speedway  principal subsidiaries  principle competitors  references  external links historyedit speedway motorsports didnt officially incorporate until  bruton smith began building smi in the s when he worked as a race promoter and eventually built charlotte motor speedway in  smith left the racing business in the early s to pursue other business ventures he became very successful and by  had owned majority shares in cms and took over as ceo a year later he appointed ha humpy wheeler as general manager smith began to expand cms adding additional grandstands and facilities including condominiums a first for a sports facility in  smith began to acquire additional speedway properties beginning with atlanta motor speedway as he did with charlotte smith began expanding seating and facilities at atlanta in  lights were added to cms making it one of the first speedways to offer night racing and the company developed the legends car racing circuit now called us legend cars international smith incorporated speedway motorsports in december  and in february th  took the company public by offering shares of stock debuting at  per share in  smi began to quickly expand acquiring two additional facilities bristol motor speedway and sonoma raceway a year later the company finished construction of the  million  seat texas motor speedway between  and  smi had increased its total seating capacity from  to  in  smi outbid rival international speedway corporation isc to purchase las vegas motor speedway smith had outbid isc by  million to make a total  million purchase that same year smi sold the naming rights of its flagship charlotte motor speedway to lowes a  million deal that would last until  until  speedway motorsports was the top track owner in the motorsports industry that year international speedway corporation then the second largest track owner acquired penske motorsports then the third largest track owner the  million deal propelled isc to the top track owner and smi fell to second smith then turned his attention towards securing two nascar dates at each of his facilities as of  only four smi owned tracks hold two nascar dates smi purchased north wilkesboro speedway and new hampshire motor speedway in  and in  purchased kentucky speedway today smi owns nine racing facilities eight of which are used to host major racing series including nascar indycar and nhra as of december   the combined total permanent seating capacity was approximately  in  smi owned tracks will host  of the  nascar sprint cup series races including three chase races plus the sprint all star race in addition to speedway properties smi also owns performance racing network a radio network that broadcasts all nascar races at smi owned tracks smi also equally owns motorsports authentics a joint venture formed with international speedway corporation to produce market and sell licensed motorsports merchandise facilities ownededit track location facility acreage main layout seating capacity year opened acquired date major series atlanta motor speedway hampton ga   miles  km quadoval    nascar bristol motor speedway bristol tn   miles  km oval    nascar nhra charlotte motor speedway concord nc   miles  km quadoval    nascar nhra woo kentucky speedway sparta ky   miles  km trioval   may   nascar las vegas motor speedway las vegas nv   miles  km d shapedoval    nascar nhra woo new hampshire motor speedway loudon nh   miles  km oval   november   nascar north wilkesboro speedway north wilkesboro nc    miles  km oval   na sonoma raceway sonoma ca   miles  km road course    nascar indycar nhra texas motor speedway fort worth tx   miles  km quadoval    built nascar indycar some facilities include multiple layouts and multiple tracks including dirt ovals and dragways notable purchasesedit smi has a history of purchasing tracks to obtain nascar race dates the companys purchases and closures of the tracks in order to obtain a second nascar date for texas motor speedway led to the ferko lawsuit north wilkesboro speedwayedit in  the company purchased half interest in north wilkesboro speedway in north wilkesboro north carolina along with bob bahre of new hampshire international speedway now new hampshire motor speedway smi moved one of north wilkesboro speedways dates to texas motor speedway and bob bahre moved the second date to his facility on november   smi purchased nhis and part of the purchase resulted in smi gaining full ownership of north wilkesboro speedway north carolina speedwayedit in  as a result of the ferko lawsuit smi gained ownership of the north carolina speedway in rockingham north carolina smi closed north carolina speedway and moved the tracks final race date to texas motor speedway on october   smi sold north carolina speedway at auction the track was purchased by indiana andy hillenburg for  million and renamed rockingham speedway new hampshire motor speedwayedit on november   smi announced the purchase of new hampshire international speedway from bob bahre and renamed the facility new hampshire motor speedway this has led to speculation that smi would move one of new hampshires dates to las vegas motor speedway andor swap the date with the fall race at texas motor speedway tms has expressed an interest in moving the fall race away from the first weekend in november which is also the opening weekend of deer hunting season in texas in  the fall race weekend will be moved to las vegas kentucky speedwayedit on may   smi announced it had purchased kentucky speedway from kentucky speedway llc it was purchased from joie chitwood the track had been trying to secure a nascar sprint cup race for several years smi was finally victorious in their pursuit with kentucky speedway receiving its inaugural sprint cup race on july   it appears this came at the expense of smiowned atlanta motor speedway which dropped from two races to one on the  sprint cup schedule principal subsidiariesedit tracks atlanta motor speedway inc bristol motor speedway inc charlotte motor speedway inc las vegas motor speedway llc spr acquisition corporation dba sears point raceway texas motor speedway inc other speedway systems llc dba finish line events  racing inc inex corporation the speedway club inc oilchem research corporation speedway funding corporation sonoma funding corporation principle competitorsedit international speedway corporation dover motorsports incorporated referencesedit  a b c history of speedway motorsports inc reference for businesses retrieved  november    a b company description speedway motorsports retrieved  november    smi purchasing new hampshire speedway freelibrary retrieved  november    speedway motorsports agrees to purchase kentucky speedway may   retrieved  november    sprint cup series to visit kentucky speedway in  kentucky speedway august   retrieved  november    atlanta motor speedway announces schedule for  nascar season august   retrieved  november   external linksedit official website company profile v t e current monster energy nascar cup series race venues isc auto club chicagoland darlington daytona homestead kansas martinsville michigan phoenix richmond talladega watkins glen smi atlanta bristol charlotte kentucky las vegas new hampshire sonoma texas other dover indianapolis pocono retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlespeedwaymotorsportsoldid categories nascarentertainment companies of the united statescompanies based in charlotte north carolinaentertainment companies established in companies listed on the new york stock exchangehidden categories pages using deprecated image syntax navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprintable version languages deutschfrançaisitalianoportuguês edit links this page was last edited on  june  at  text is available under the creative commons attributionsharealike license additional terms may apply by using this site you agree to the terms of use and privacy policy wikipedia® is a registered trademark of the wikimedia foundation inc a nonprofit organization privacy policy about wikipedia disclaimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view speedway motorsports  wikipedia speedway motorsports from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from speedway motorsports inc jump to navigation search speedway motorsports type public traded as nyse trk industry motorsports founded  headquarters concord north 